  "response_text": "A smiling adult woman with short dark brown hair and large round tinted eyeglasses is shown in a warm, softly lit indoor setting. She wears a light-colored blouse and looks down toward a spoonful of yellow cake near her mouth. A white lower-third caption identifies her by name and location, with “Houston, Texas” visible. She raises the spoon, smiling with anticipation, opens her mouth, takes the bite, and then draws the spoon out while chewing, her expression relaxed and pleased.\n\nAnother adult woman appears next, with reddish hair styled up and small dangling earrings. She wears a patterned blouse and looks down toward her spoon. A white caption at the lower left identifies her as “Jane Trahan” from “Scottsboro, Alabama.” She brings a spoonful of cake to her mouth, takes the bite, and closes her lips around the spoon, then smiles subtly as she tastes it.\n\nThe focus shifts to a white plate on a warm-toned tabletop holding a thick slice of layered yellow cake with dark chocolate frosting between the layers and around the outside. A metal spoon presses into the front edge of the slice and scoops out a soft bite, showing the pale yellow crumb inside. The spoon lifts the bite away from the cake, leaving a neat hollow in the slice and a bit of frosting clinging to the cake and spoon.\n\nA box of Pillsbury Plus Yellow Cake mix fills the scene against a pink-red background. The package is cream-colored with a dark round Pillsbury logo near the upper left and large black lettering reading “Pillsbury Plus.” Smaller text reads “Yellow Cake” and “There’s Pudding in the Mix.” The front of the box shows a photograph of yellow cake with chocolate frosting, including a spoon lifting a frosted bite. Across the lower part of the screen, white text reads, “Ingredients added, according to directions.” A spoonful of cake briefly enters near the right side of the box, visually connecting the product package to the tasting.\n\nAnother adult woman, with medium brown hair and a plaid blouse, is shown in a softly blurred home-like interior. A lower-third caption identifies her as “Pat Lundquist” from “Shawnee Mission, Kansas.” She opens her mouth for a spoonful of cake, takes the bite, and closes her lips around the spoon. Her face remains calm and absorbed as she tastes.\n\nA fourth adult woman with light brown, shoulder-length hair appears, seated in a warm, dim interior. A caption identifies her as “Linda Suter” from “Norcross, Georgia.” She holds a spoonful of cake near her face while looking forward, then turns her attention to the spoon and takes a bite. Her hand, with a ring visible, guides the spoon to her mouth, and she withdraws it as she begins to chew.\n\nThe Pillsbury Plus Yellow Cake box returns, again showing the large “Pillsbury Plus” name and the phrase “There’s Pudding in the Mix” on the front. The cake photo on the package remains prominent, with the yellow cake and dark frosting presented as moist and soft-looking. A spoonful of cake passes near the top edge of the package.\n\nA rapid series of very tight views follows, focusing on mouths and spoons rather than full faces. Different women open their mouths as spoons carrying small yellow cake bites approach. The cake pieces look soft and crumbly, sometimes with a bit of darker frosting attached. Each bite is placed into the mouth, the lips close around the spoon, and the spoon slides out cleanly. The repeated images emphasize the act of tasting: open mouth, spoonful of yellow cake, bite taken, spoon withdrawn.\n\nThe commercial ends on the Pillsbury Plus Yellow Cake box, held steadily against the warm red-pink background. The cream-colored package, dark Pillsbury logo, bold “Pillsbury Plus” lettering, “Yellow Cake,” and “There’s Pudding in the Mix” remain clearly visible, along with the appetizing picture of the frosted yellow cake on the front.",
